{"sequenceId":"845362389561","id":"34207118032","language":"English","title":"Pope Francis to discuss climate change with oil company CEOs","content":"Bloomberg/London/Rome     Oil company bosses will travel to the Vatican this week to discuss climate change with Pope Francis.  The meeting will be on June 8 and June 9 at the Casina Pio IV villa in the Vatican, with an audience with the Pope on the second day, according to a spokesman. It is being organized by a department headed by Cardinal Peter Turkson, who helped write Pope Francis’ 2015 encyclical on climate.  “We look forward to the dialogue, and the opportunity to discuss how we can address climate change and opportunities in the energy transition,” a spokesman for Equinor ASA, Norway’s largest oil company, said in an e-mailed statement on Friday.  BP chief executive officer Bob Dudley will also travel to Rome for the meeting arranged by the University of Notre Dame, according to people familiar with the talks. The Pope has made climate change a cornerstone of his papacy, saying in an encyclical letter that the science around the topic is clear and that the Catholic Church should view it as a moral issue.  A spokeswoman for BP declined to comment. Exxon Mobil Corp and Eni SpA will also participate in the meeting, according to reports from Axios and Reuters. A spokesman for Royal Dutch Shell declined to comment on whether its CEO would be involved.  The University of Notre Dame didn’t respond to requests for comment.","contentWithMarkup":"Bloomberg/London/Rome     Oil company bosses will travel to the Vatican this week to discuss climate change with Pope Francis.  The meeting will be on June 8 and June 9 at the Casina Pio IV villa in the Vatican, with an audience with the Pope on the second day, according to a spokesman. It is being organized by a department headed by Cardinal Peter Turkson, who helped write Pope Francis’ 2015 encyclical on climate.  “We look forward to the dialogue, and the opportunity to discuss how we can address climate change and opportunities in the energy transition,” a spokesman for Equinor ASA, Norway’s largest oil company, said in an e-mailed statement on Friday.  BP chief executive officer Bob Dudley will also travel to Rome for the meeting arranged by the University of Notre Dame, according to people familiar with the talks. The Pope has made climate change a cornerstone of his papacy, saying in an encyclical letter that the science around the topic is clear and that the Catholic Church should view it as a moral issue.  A spokeswoman for BP declined to comment. Exxon Mobil Corp and Eni SpA will also participate in the meeting, according to reports from Axios and Reuters. A spokesman for Royal Dutch Shell declined to comment on whether its CEO would be involved.  The University of Notre Dame didn’t respond to requests for comment.","tags":[],"publishedDate":"2018-06-03T00:20:51Z","harvestDate":"2018-06-02T21:26:07Z","estimatedPublishedDate":"2018-06-02T21:26:07Z","url":"http://ct.moreover.com/?a=34207118032&p=1u0&v=1&x=o9IjVs_ugdOmg3w-7BKJ-g","originalUrl":"http://www.gulf-times.com/story/594890/Pope-Francis-to-discuss-climate-change-with-oil-co","outboundUrls":[],"wordCount":"225","dataFormat":"text","duplicateGroupId":"34199698043","media":{"audio":[],"images":[{"url":"http://img.gulf-times.com/Content/Upload/Slider/62018302022918056626.jpg"}],"video":[],"logo":[]},"publishingPlatform":{},"adultLanguage":"false","topics":[{"name":"Energy industry news","group":"Industry"},{"name":"Oil and gas news","group":"Industry"},{"name":"BP news","group":"Companies"},{"name":"Climate change news","group":"Science"},{"name":"Weather news","group":"Science"},{"name":"Environment news","group":"Science"},{"name":"Religion news","group":"Society"}],"companies":[{"name":"Eni SpA","symbol":"ENI","exchange":"DUS","isin":"IT0003132476","titleCount":0,"contentCount":1,"primary":true},{"name":"Eni SpA","symbol":"ENI","exchange":"MUN","isin":"IT0003132476","titleC